han one\nCepheid member at any given time, in particular at a lower metallicity. We\ninterpret the results as outcomes of various aspects of star cluster dynamics.\nThe comparison of predicted and observed clustered Cepheid fractions, $f_{\\rm\nCC}$, highlights the need for additional cluster disruption mechanisms, most\nlikely encounters with giant molecular clouds.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 16 Dec 2021 19:04:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-23"}
